  "texts": [
    "In human expert qualitative analysis, the 4C metrics were compared by a one-sample Wilcoxon signed-rank test 13, and the agreement of ratings between experts was assessed by Fleiss' kappa coefficient 45, and interpreted as recommended by Landis et al 46.",
    "We conducted Pearson correlation analyses to explore the relationships between each human expert evaluation metric, assessing their independence.",
    "Additionally, we conducted similar analyses to examine the correlation between human and automatic metrics.",
    "All the comparisons consider a p-value < 0.05 as significant.",
    "Our development set contains 97,506 reports from 71,717 unique patients with a mean age of 64.1±16.1 years, and 38,912 (54.3%) were male."
  ],
